<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-648-558  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 648 558.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC-Computing  August 1990 v3 n8 p40(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>What's going on in that PC? Put System Sleuth on the case.andO;(Software Review) (Dariana Technology Group System Sleuthdiagnostic software)</TITLE><AUTHOR>White, Ron.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Dariana Technology Group Inc. (products).andO;Product:   System Sleuth 2.1 (Performance analysis software) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     DiagnosticsMicrocomputersUtility ProgramsEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>System Sleuth Version 2.1 is a slick detective, investigating the goings-onin every nook of your PC system, from memory to bus to disk drives.andM;The new, $149 version improves on the old by more thoroughly Snooping throughany section of RAM to read what's there in hex or ASCII format.andP;  It can tellyou which interrupts are being trapped by TSR programs, which parts of memoryare being used by programs and hardware, which memory areas work fastest, andwhich are being used by memory managers to swap data.andP;  This version alsolooks into hardware, identifying your hard drive configuration and interruptsand I/O addresses that are used by expansion boards.andM;In PC/Computing tests, the program worked without a hitch, except that itdidn't recognize a 486 processor.andP;  DTG says a new version is on the way tocorrect that oversight.andM;An information Source only, System Sleuth doesn't change any part Of yoursystem's Configuration-a good thing, as the ability to write to SOme areas ofthe system could crash your PC or even alter the FAT, losing data on the harddisk.andP;  The problem, then, is making sense of the data that System Sleuthunearths.andP;  Tutorials in the manual can help, and DTG's advanced technicalsupport offers 20 calls to a toll-free number for support and interpretationof results, as well as a 24-hour bulletin board.andP;  The support costs  100 ayear.andM;In addition to System Sleuth itself, the Program disk includes a number ofstandard utilities, such as a 386 memory manager, a disk cache, afile-finder, and a program to record and restore your system's CMOS settings.andO;But don't buy this electronic gumshoe for its utilities; buy it for itsdetective work.andP;  RON WHITE</TEXT></DOC>